nnects your door from its motor.";i:46;s:63:"Raise your garage door about halfway up to the middle position.";i:47;s:189:"Like most items that live out in the elements garage door springs become susceptible to problems during extreme weather and regular maintenance is key to keep them running in tip-top shape.";i:48;s:86:"This post looks at a few of the reasons you may be having garage door spring problems.";i:49;s:63:"Here are our top 4 reasons garage door spring repair is needed.";i:50;s:60:"Panic sets in as Willie scrambles for the fire extinguisher.";i:51;s:153:"When your door does not work then it can cause you to miss work show up late for an appointment or keep you from putting your vehicle back in the garage.";i:52;s:66:"If your door does not open then it most likely is a broken spring.";i:53;s:89:"Your door will not open back up until you have someone replace the faulty torsion spring.";}}